(
<figureCitation box="[1072,1197,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="18.[132,143,1940,1957]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[698,1267,768,1324]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIG. 12. — Helochelydrid and thalassochelydian turtle remains from Angeac-Charente: A, peripheral plate of Helochelydridae indet. in dorsal view;B, pleural plate of Helochelydridae indet. in dorsal view; C, D, right hyoplastron of Hylaeochelys belli? (Mantell, 1844) (ANG18-5915) in ventral (C) and dorsal (D) views; E, left humerus of Hylaeochelys? belli? (ANG18-5937) in ventral view; F, right humerus (ANG18-5938) in dorsal view;; G, H, Peripheral of Hylaeochelys? belli? (ANG 18-5993) in dorsal (G) and ventral (H) views. Scale bar: A, 1 cm; E-H, 2 cm; B, 3 cm; C, D, 4 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902061/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="697">Fig. 12A, B</figureCitation>
